	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>What to Expect During Your Check-up</h2>
		<p>We pride ourselves on making every check-up a comfortable, educational, and completely stress-free experience. A standard hygiene appointment includes:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Comprehensive Examination:</strong> Our dentists will carefully inspect your teeth for decay, check your existing fillings, and perform a routine oral cancer screening.</li>
			<li><strong>Digital X-Rays:</strong> When necessary, we use low-radiation digital X-rays to see what is happening below the gumline and between the teeth.</li>
			<li><strong>Professional Scaling & Polishing:</strong> Our skilled hygienists will gently remove hardened tartar (calculus) and plaque, finishing with a polish to remove surface stains caused by coffee or tea.</li>
			<li><strong>Fluoride Treatment (Optional):</strong> A quick fluoride application helps remineralize enamel and make your teeth more resistant to acid attacks.</li>
			<li><strong>Personalized Oral Hygiene Advice:</strong> We will provide actionable tips and recommend the best products to improve your daily brushing and flossing routine.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<div class="faq">
			<details>
				<summary>How often should I get my teeth cleaned?</summary>
				<p>The <a href="https://www.cda-adc.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Canadian Dental Association</a> generally recommends a professional cleaning and exam every 6 months. However, if you have a history of periodontal (gum) disease, heavy tartar buildup, or are currently undergoing orthodontic treatment, we might suggest coming in every 3 to 4 months to maintain optimal health.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Does getting your teeth cleaned hurt?</summary>
				<p>For most patients, a dental cleaning is completely painless. If you have sensitive teeth or inflamed gums, let our hygienist know beforehand. We can use desensitizing pastes or adjust our techniques to ensure you remain totally comfortable.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Does the CDCP or private insurance cover dental cleanings?</summary>
				<p>Yes! Preventive services like scaling, polishing, and exams are standard benefits covered by the CDCP (for eligible patients) and almost all private extended health insurance plans. We handle the direct billing to make your visit hassle-free.</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</section>

